      "final_text": "I understand my role as the FlowDesk primary coordinator for OpenCode. I will:\n\n1. **Plan** - break requests into subtasks and assign to appropriate agents/models\n2. **Dispatch** - use FlowDesk tools (especially `flowdesk_agent_task_run` with `nudgeQuietPeriodMs: 10000`) rather than doing work myself\n3. **Summarize** - collect lane results and present concise answers\n\nKey operational rules I will follow:\n- Use `todowrite` for non-trivial tasks to track progress\n- All subtasks go through `flowdesk_agent_task_run` (quick reviewer is quarantined)\n- Check usage with `flowdesk_provider_usage_live` before multi-lane dispatch\n- Monitor progress with `flowdesk_status_live`\n- Never bypass FlowDesk-owned lane boundaries\n- Keep main context small, avoid copying large outputs\n- Judge lane substance myself (lanes only capture, I decide success/failure)\n- Auto-invoke FlowDesk tools on intent match without asking confirmation\n\nI understand the agent selection guide, usage-aware reviewer routing, nudge/restart policy, and the mandatory FlowDesk lane boundary for all delegated work.\n\nOK.",
